.TH "__pci_device_probe" 9 "__pci_device_probe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__pci_device_probe \- check if a driver wants to claim a specific PCI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __pci_device_probe
.BI "(struct pci_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct pci_dev *pci_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
driver to call to check if it wants the PCI device
.IP "pci_dev" 12
PCI device being probed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
returns 0 on success, else error.
side-effect: pci_dev->driver is set to drv when drv claims pci_dev.
